###8. Turkey Meatloaf & Mashed Potatoes

<%= partial "partials/image.erb", locals: {
     url: "https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B018SRHFO0/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=bonktothefi07-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&linkCode=as2&creativeASIN=B018SRHFO0&linkId=8b51bab774f3dac9b042dc77f3efc924",
     src: "luvo-turkey-meatloaf.jpg",
     alt: "Luvo Inc. Frozen Meals Turkey Meatloaf & Mashed Potatoes"} %>

This one was not as exciting as Luvo's other options.
That's not to say it isn't good, but it isn't as unique as a planted bowl or tandoori-inspired chicken.
This meal would be ideal for picky eaters or those who are not as adventurous.

I got this meal twice, the second time the meal had been redesigned slightly.
There were no longer massive brussel sprouts chunks in the meal.
They were replaced with collared greens.
This was an improvement in my opinion, although I try I still cannot seem to like brussel sprouts.

###Final Thoughts

In summary, I thought that these meals tasted fresh and had good variety.
Each meal was low in calories which is good for weight maintenance/loss.
However as I was reaching my peak training for my 100 miler, I found that I needed snacks in addition to these meals.

My favorite meal was the Hawaiian Un-Fried Rice bowl.
I wish stores near me carried more of the planted bowls.
I also heard good things about the Roasted Cauliflower Mac & Cheese.
Those are the meals still on my list to try!

Luvo now has an [online store front](https://shop.luvoinc.com/) where you can get free shipping if you order at least 15 meals.
This sounds like a great alternative to driving around town to try all the different meals that they offer!

